&lt;p&gt;We also offer a warm and inclusive work environment that embraces a hybrid employment model, blending an in office presence and work from home experience for our valued employees. The hiring team will go over these expectations with you if you are being considered for a role near one of our offices in San Francisco, Los Angeles, Chicago, Dallas, New York, and London.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Impact&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; You’ll Make&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you want the challenge of learning, working, and growing in compensation, the satisfaction of seeing your work come to life, and the pride in helping grow a world-class team, this is the place for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your responsibilities will include:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Designing, building, and maintaining compensation tooling and dashboards to deliver insights that guide compensation decisions&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting cyclical and ongoing programs including compensation planning and review cycles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conducting market research and analysis for compensation, including participating in market compensation surveys and maintaining of global benchmarks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Building and maintaining financial models and running scenario analysis to support compensation program development and alignment with company goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participating in a variety of compensation and people related projects, including building tools and refining processes to help all of Nextdoor work efficiently and productively together&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in in-person Nextdoor events such as trainings, off-sites, volunteer days, and team building exercises&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build in-person relationships with team members and contribute to Nextdoor’s company culture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
